
Forward Proxy
Definition: Proxy in front of clients
Flow: Client → Proxy → Server
Use: Control outgoing traffic
Example: Corporate proxy, VPN

Reverse Proxy
Definition: Proxy in front of servers
Flow: Client → Proxy → Servers
Use: Route & protect incoming traffic
Example: NGINX, HAProxy, ALB

API Gateway
Definition: Reverse proxy for APIs/microservices
Flow: Client → Gateway → Services
Use: Auth, rate-limit, route APIs
Example: AWS API Gateway, Kong

One-line Difference
Forward Proxy → hides clients
Reverse Proxy → hides servers
API Gateway → manages APIs